03/03/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government announced plans to expand participation in NATO by providing special units for nuclear, chemical and biological defence to the Allied rapid reaction force. The decision followed talks Wednesday (2 March) between Bulgarian Army chief General Nikola Kolev and NATO's Supreme Allied Commander for Transformation, Admiral Edmund Giambastiani. The admiral praised the success of military reforms in Bulgaria, which joined the Pact last year, and stressed Sofia's contribution to peacekeeping missions abroad. (Sega - 03/03/05; Bulgarian government Web site, Mediapool - 02/03/05)
